SUMMARY:Living Authentically
DESCRIPTION:Courage is not the beginning of self-knowledge. It is the constant condition of it. \nCourage to Be You follows two people asking that question from very different lives. Amit and Najib are a gay couple navigating not only their relationship but the religious and social distance between them. Rajeshwari\, Amit’s childhood friend\, is quietly working to reclaim an identity fractured by early trauma. Their stories run parallel\, but their questions are the same: what does it take to choose yourself\, and what do you risk when you do? \nRashna Imhasly-Gandhy draws on Jungian psychology and chakra healing\, offering the reader a framework for the same inner work her characters undertake. Their guide\, in both cases\, is a therapist. Their destination is their own. \nYasmeen Premji will introduce the session. Rashna’s presentation will be followed by a conversation between her and Malini White. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/living-authentically/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Gender,Health & Wellness,Philosophy,Society
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_LA.jpg
END:VEVENT
