SUMMARY:The Cities We Carry
DESCRIPTION:Two questions plagued her for five years\, living between Delhi\, Venice\, and Istanbul: how do we lose what we lose\, and why do we love whom we love? \nDrawing on her collection of essays Place: Intimate Encounters with Cities (2026)\, written across 25 years and 13 cities\, Ananya Vajpeyi will explore what cities hold for us.  The memory and meaning held in street corners and corridors of light; the way personal loss and political trouble have of finding each other in the very same spaces. \nArchitect Prem Chandavarkar brings his own lifelong reckoning with cities to the table. Between them\, the conversation promises to move across continents\, disciplines\, and the question of what it means to love a place. \nThe conversation will be followed by a Q&A with the audience. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-cities-we-carry/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Cities
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_TCWC.jpg
END:VEVENT
