UID:86364-1772737200-1772742600@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Beyond Accompaniment
DESCRIPTION:The harmonium has spent centuries being useful. \nIt has held the shruti\, supported the vocalist\, filled the space between phrases with something steady and unobtrusive. It has been\, in the best possible sense\, reliable. What it has rarely been given is the stage to itself. \nThis recital does exactly that. The programme traverses khayal\, thumri\, tappa\, dhun\, theatre music\, and devotional compositions\, moving between gayaki ang and tantrakari ang\, the vocal and instrumental traditions. One segment demonstrates how a shift in genre changes the technique\, the phrasing\, the entire interpretive logic of the instrument. The kind of detail that makes you realise you have never quite listened to it before. \nThe harmonium\, it turns out\, has been waiting. And this is its debut. \nSupported by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/beyond-accompaniment/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-114.jpg
END:VEVENT
